{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2014}} '''Karmel Kandreva''' ({{lang-it|Carmelo Candreva}};<ref name="PynsentKanikova1993">{{cite book|author1=Robert B. Pynsent|author2=Sonia I. Kanikova|title=Reader's encyclopedia of Eastern European literature|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Z4kYAAAAIAAJ|date=April 1993|publisher=HarperCollins|isbn=978-0-06-270007-0}}</ref> 1931–1982) was an [[Arbëreshë people|Arberesh]] writer and poet.<ref name="Shkurtaj1984">{{cite book|author=Gjovalin Shkurtaj|title=Shpirti i arbrit rron|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=_pESAgAAQBAJ&pg=PT32|date=1 May 1984|publisher=Artjon Shkurtaj|pages=32–|id=GGKEY:46CPC19D5K4}}</ref><ref name="Shqipërisëshqiptar1985">{{cite book|author1=Akademia e Shkencave e RPS të Shqipërisë|author2=Fjalori enciklopedik shqiptar|title=Fjalor enciklopedik shqiptar|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=NDNBAQAAIAAJ|year=1985|publisher=[[Akademia e Shkencave e RPSSH]]| oclc=15296028}}</ref>
He was born in [[Cerzeto]] (''Qanë'') in [[Calabria]], Italy. Among his published works is a study ''Didactic test in a bilingual Arberesh environment'', about the right of the Arberesh people to cultivate their own language and to have it taught at schools.<ref name="Shkurtaj1984"/>
He also published several [[poetry|poetical]] volumes.
