The '''Karon language''' is an [[endangered language]] of [[Senegal]] and [[Gambia]].  It belongs to the [[Bak languages|Bak]] branch of the [[Niger–Congo languages|Niger–Congo]] language family, and is particularly closely related to the [[Mlomp language]].

