{{Infobox language |name=Maleng |altname=Pakatan |nativename=Bo |states=[[Laos]], [[Vietnam]] |speakers=3,700 |date=2000–2007 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Austro-Asiatic |fam2=[[Vietic languages|Vietic]] |dia1=Atel |dia2=Thémarou |dia3=Arao |dia4=Makang |dia5=Malang |dia6=Maleng |dia7=Tơe |lc1=pkt|ld1=Pakatan |lc2=bgl|ld2=Bo |glotto=male1282 |glottoname=Maleng |glotto2=bola1249 |glottoname2=Bo }}
'''Maleng''', also known as '''Pakatan''' and '''Bo''', is a [[Vietic language]] of Laos and Vietnam.
Maleng has the four-way [[register (phonology)|register]] system of [[Thavung language|Thavung]] augmented with [[tone (linguistics)|pitch]].[http://sealang.net/mk/vietic.htm]
''Malieng'', despite having the same name as Maleng, is a dialect of [[Chut language|Chut]] (Chamberlain 2003, Sidwell 2009).
