The '''(Western) Omo–Tana''' languages belong to the [[Afro-Asiatic languages|Afro-Asiatic]] family and are spoken in [[Ethiopia]] and [[Kenya]].  The [[El Molo language|El Molo]] language of Kenya is nearly extinct.<ref>Raymond G. Gordon Jr., ed.  2005.  ''Ethnologue:  Languages of the World''.  15th edition.  Dallas:  Summer Institute of Linguistics.</ref>

